<section id="reverting-changes-in-an-editor" version="5.0" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
                                                           xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
                                                           xmlns:xl="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" >
  <title>Reverting changes in an editor</title>
  <anchor role="helpid" id="guidancerSpecTestCaseEditorContextId">Test Case Editor</anchor>
  <anchor role="helpid" id="testSuiteEditorContextId">Test Suite Editor</anchor>
  <anchor role="helpid" id="guidancerTestJobEditorContextId">Test Job Editor</anchor>
  <para>
    You can revert an editor you are working in to the state of the last save.
  </para>
  <orderedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        In the editor you are in, right-click and select:
        
        <para>
          <emphasis role="menuPath">Revert changes</emphasis>
        </para>
        
        from the context sensitive menu.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Confirm that you want to revert the changes when prompted.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        The editor will be reverted. Any changes you have made since
        the last save will be lost.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </orderedlist>
</section>